There are a few things that come to mind regarding this app;
One would be, if I'm storing FIAT on an account with this app, what sort of return am I getting? It's essentially me lending money until I use it, so I'd like to get something in return. If not, I see no reason to "store" my FIAT here.
Second, are there any transfer fees? This is pretty important when running an app like this, I know coinbase charges quite a bit which turns people off of investing anything under a certain amount, ~$100.
Third, am I able to sell my coins back to the system? If I do that, I'd be trading from FIAT to crypto over and over so many times, my taxes would be ridiculously high, since not only would I need to pay taxes on any payouts, which would be every time I sold my bitcoin for USD, but I'd also need to pay taxes on any like to like trades since crypto is considered property by the IRS. 
Just some things to consider.
I like a platform that will allow you to invest small amounts of money. Even a small return is a good return and if you gain nothing, you have lost little! Thank you!
